Thaums and thaumic radiation. As a former library, the building would have been exposed to L-Space, which is well known for bleeding thaums into the surrounding environment. Active libraries have special shielding in the walls to minimize the impact of this thaum-bleed but that shielding tends to break down over the years, so the thaumic bleedover from L-Space likely created a waste pit.

And remember, never call an orangutan a monkey.









